If there are only 2 groups in the zone (Gnoll and Orc) then your left with very few other options than to move on or go on the long waiting lists... Both camps there have a named spawn that are still very popular... Gnolls have the Polished Granite Tomahawk and the Orcs have the Shiny Brass Halbert or the much coveted weight reduction bag. The up side is too keep all the Gnoll scalps to turn in to the guard near the camp there for some nice faction adjustments in all Qeynos guards and other places...<br>
<br>
Its pretty much the same story inside HHK. The basement has 3 camp spots really. Keep the goblin ears for more faction adjustments... The spawn rate is pretty fast in the rooms but again the list to join can be long.<br>
<br>
At 15-18 another spot to get rolling for a pally is Kurn tower in Feild of bone... Your anti-undead magics will serve you well in there. The Zone is not camped very heavy... Typ there are 4 people... 3 of them will be level 58-60 camping something in the basement I think. The down side is the long walk back to FV for supplies...<br>
<br>
Your anti-undead ability should pull you to places like Unrest/Befallen as well.<br>
<br>
I would vote for DL over L Guk. Dreadlands supports MANY camps and has a good group of people looking for healers and Melee all the time... 40-51 are often best spent there. The added draws to this location is easy access to the Nexus to get yourself around easier than taking any of the boats. FV is next door through the tunnel. You'll be camping North Wall at Karnors... So you can start getting groups going in there and getting great EXP and graduate to there after level 46-50.<br>
<br>
There are some great camps on Luclin now as well for all levels... Personally I'm exploring them ATM. The camps are pretty light there and access to most of Norath is only a hop skip and jump with the Nexus access so close.<br>
<br>
Anyhow... Back on focus... I would tend to lead you to Kunark zones... There is typically undead available in most zones... The groups are more available and people you build a rep with will tend to move through the areas as you do so yu get to work with the same people more often. You can start to see who is better to group with and I can't say enough about this... Finding a good group you can move through levels with is one of the more important things I would advise.<br>
<br>
My Pally Gwayn will be moving to Kunark as soon as he gets finished grinding in N. Karana.<br>
<br>
PS: levels 28-40 can be spent in Great divide on the Tizmats and then on the Giants. The loot is pretty good (for a non-twink) and the dragon faction will pay off later in SF, CS, ToV and DN raids... Not to mention zoning into WW unagroed with dragon up or running through DL without Gore trying to kill you...lol<br>
<br>
Well I hope this gives you some options...<br>
